@node Bench "Benchmark"

                         Benchmark 1.2


Benchmark is a small programm that not only shows how the library but it
also calculates some "basic" benchmarks (Now THAT is news, isnt it :).

When run it will start doing some test using 50 database files that is
created in the current directory and output the results to stdout (usualy
the shellwindow from where it was started even if it can be run from
WorkBench).

    ----------------- Example output ------------------

Creating databases...
Took: 6.527 (7/sec)

Closing databases...
Took: 0.140 (357/sec)

Opens databases...
Took: 1.907 (26/sec)

Creating new nodes...
Took: 0.118 (423/sec)

Storing 10 integrers in node...
Took: 0.005 (10000/sec)

Storing 10 strings in node...
Took: 0.018 (2777/sec)

Writing data to disk...
Took: 2.613 (19/sec)

Flushing cache...
Took: 0.016 (3125/sec)

Loading nodes...
Took: 0.696 (71/sec)

Reading data...
Took: 0.001 (50000/sec)

Releasing nodes...
Took: 0.001 (50000/sec)

Geting nodes from cache...
Took: 0.002 (25000/sec)

Deleteing nodes...
Took: 1.995 (25/sec)

Closing databases...
Took: 2.332 (21/sec)

Deleting files...

    -------------- End of output ---------------

The given number are first the total number of seconds the operation took
(divide by 50 to get the time/database) and the second are the time
recalculated into number of operations per second.

